Assignment: Build a "DevCon 2025" Conference Landing Page

Objective:
Design and code a single HTML page for the fictional "DevCon 2025" tech conference.
The page must demonstrate use of the following HTML elements:

Required HTML Elements:

1. Text formatting tags:
   - <h1> to <h6>, <p>, <strong>, <em>

2. Semantic structure tags:
   - <header>, <nav>, <main>, <section>, <article>, <aside>, <footer>

3. Hyperlinks:
   - <a>

4. Tables:
   - <table>, <caption>, <thead>, <tbody>, <th>, <td>

5. Lists:
   - <ul>, <ol>, <li>, or <dl>, <dt>, <dd>

6. Layout containers:
   - <div>, <span> with simple CSS class hooks

7. Forms:
   - <form>, <label>, <input>, <select>, <option>, <textarea>, <button>

-----------------------------------------------------

Input Data to Use:

Conference Name:
DevCon 2025

Tagline:
Exploring the Future of Development

Navigation Menu (href should link to these section IDs):
- Home (#home)
- Speakers (#speakers)
- Schedule (#schedule)
- Register (#register)
- Contact (#contact)

Introduction Paragraph (in <article id="home">):
DevCon 2025 brings together developers, engineers, and tech leaders 
for two days of hands-on workshops and visionary keynotes.

Speakers (in <section id="speakers">):
- Alice Johnson: https://alice.example.com
- Bob Smith: https://bob.example.com
- Carol Lee: https://carol.example.com

Schedule (in <section id="schedule">):
Table with caption: DevCon 2025 Schedule
Columns: Time | Session | Speaker(s)
Rows:
1. 09:00–10:00 | Keynote: The Next Big Thing | Alice Johnson, Bob Smith, Carol Lee
2. 10:15–11:00 | Panel: AI in 2025

Ticket Types (used in both <aside> and form <select>):
- Regular: $199
- Student: $99
- VIP: $399

-----------------------------------------------------

Expected Output Structure:

1. Header (<header>)
   - <h1> with "DevCon 2025"
   - Tagline in <p> with <strong> or <em>
   - <nav> with links to all sections

2. Main Content (<main>)
   - <article id="home">: Introduction paragraph
   - <section id="speakers">:
     - <h2>Speakers</h2>
     - <ul> with clickable speaker names linking to URLs
   - <section id="schedule">:
     - <h2>Schedule</h2>
     - <table> with a caption and 2 session rows
   - <section id="register">:
     - <h2>Register</h2>
     - <form>:
       - Text inputs: Name, Email
       - <select> for Ticket Type
       - <input type="checkbox"> for session attendance
       - <button>Submit</button>

3. Sidebar (<aside> or <div class="sidebar">)
   - <dl> showing ticket types and prices

4. Footer (<footer id="contact">)
   - Contact instructions: "Email us at ..."
   - Link: social media or "Back to top"

5. Layout Wrapping:
   - Use <div> containers to group:
     - Header
     - Main + Aside
     - Footer
   - Prefer semantic tags over <div> where possible
